    "body": "### Problem\n\nSince Neovim was bumped to version 0.12.0 or later, I’m seeing a strange input bug on Ubuntu 24.04 under Wayland (Sway). When I press Enter or Backspace, Neovim registers the key press and release as two separate key presses, so the action happens twice. Downgrading to a version below 0.12.0 fixes the issue. I tested on a fresh reinstall of Ubuntu 24.04, and the problem still occurs. This happens with both the Snap package and the official AppImage from GitHub. I also tried a self-compiled version (f562204a5cd0949376102f85a250c842e5951af4), but it also includes this bug.\n\n**Logs**\n```\nWRN 2026-05-04T09:02:12.212 ui.23584   tui_handle_term_mode:226: TUI: terminal mode 69 unavailable, state 0\nWRN 2026-05-04T09:02:12.212 ui.23584   tui_handle_term_mode:239: TUI: terminal mode 2026 detected, state 2\nWRN 2026-05-04T09:02:12.212 ui.23584   tui_handle_term_mode:239: TUI: terminal mode 2027 detected, state 1\nWRN 2026-05-04T09:02:12.212 ui.23584   tui_handle_term_mode:226: TUI: terminal mode 2031 unavailable, state 0\nWRN 2026-05-04T09:02:12.212 ui.23584   tui_handle_term_mode:226: TUI: terminal mode 2048 unavailable, state 0\nWRN 2026-05-06T13:36:57.994 ui.11007   tui_handle_term_mode:226: TUI: terminal mode 69 unavailable, state 0\nWRN 2026-05-06T13:36:57.995 ui.11007   tui_handle_term_mode:239: TUI: terminal mode 2026 detected, state 2\nWRN 2026-05-06T13:36:57.995 ui.11007   tui_handle_term_mode:239: TUI: terminal mode 2027 detected, state 1\nWRN 2026-05-06T13:36:57.995 ui.11007   tui_handle_term_mode:226: TUI: terminal mode 2031 unavailable, state 0\nWRN 2026-05-06T13:36:57.995 ui.11007   tui_handle_term_mode:226: TUI: terminal mode 2048 unavailable, state 0\n```\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nOn Ubuntu 24.04 using Wayland (Sway), start Neovim:\nnvim --clean\nOpen any buffer and press Enter or Backspace.\nObserve that the key is handled twice (as if press+release are counted as two presses).\n\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nPressing Enter or Backspace in Insertion Mode should trigger a single action per key press.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.13.0-dev-430+gf562204a5c\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, 9.1\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nUbuntu 24.04\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nfoot\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nfoot\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage / snap / compiled",
